WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:01:08.239 --> 00:01:09.760
We are A.A.Murakami

00:01:11.840 --> 00:01:13.360
and we are launching

00:01:13.360 --> 00:01:15.199
a new installation called

00:01:15.199 --> 00:01:16.800
The Moon Underwater

00:01:16.800 --> 00:01:18.599
at the Mori Art Museum

00:01:18.599 --> 00:01:19.719
in central Tokyo.

00:01:22.119 --> 00:01:23.360
The Moon Underwater

00:01:23.360 --> 00:01:24.840
is the most technically

00:01:24.840 --> 00:01:26.000
ambitious project we've

00:01:26.000 --> 00:01:27.360
attempted to date.

00:01:32.960 --> 00:01:34.599
We work with

00:01:34.599 --> 00:01:36.320
fleeting states of matter,

00:01:36.320 --> 00:01:38.400
so where you meet the work

00:01:38.400 --> 00:01:39.320
isn't through

00:01:39.320 --> 00:01:41.039
technology interfaces,

00:01:41.559 --> 00:01:43.199
like screens or projections,

00:01:43.199 --> 00:01:43.719
but in fact

00:01:43.719 --> 00:01:44.719
it's through bubbles

00:01:44.719 --> 00:01:46.199
and fog rings and plasma.

00:01:49.840 --> 00:01:50.719
For this piece

00:01:50.719 --> 00:01:52.519
we were inspired by the

00:01:52.519 --> 00:01:53.599
Japanese tradition

00:01:53.599 --> 00:01:55.159
of moon-viewing,

00:01:55.159 --> 00:01:56.559
which is the

00:01:56.559 --> 00:01:58.480
appreciation of the moon

00:01:58.480 --> 00:02:00.320
and how it is considered

00:02:00.320 --> 00:02:01.800
to be the most beautiful

00:02:01.800 --> 00:02:02.800
when it's seen

00:02:02.800 --> 00:02:04.320
in reflection in water.

00:02:04.639 --> 00:02:06.440
So we wanted to

00:02:06.440 --> 00:02:07.639
create this kind of

00:02:07.639 --> 00:02:09.159
nocturnal garden

00:02:09.159 --> 00:02:10.679
to capture this feeling.

00:02:13.920 --> 00:02:14.920
What people don't see

00:02:14.920 --> 00:02:15.639
is actually

00:02:15.639 --> 00:02:17.039
behind the surface.

00:02:17.639 --> 00:02:19.239
We need the systems

00:02:19.239 --> 00:02:20.719
to operate autonomously,

00:02:20.719 --> 00:02:22.840
but entropy still creeps in.

00:02:22.840 --> 00:02:25.480
Systems will run smoothly

00:02:25.480 --> 00:02:27.079
until they encounter

00:02:27.079 --> 00:02:28.199
the unpredictable.

00:02:28.199 --> 00:02:30.039
And so we're able to

00:02:30.039 --> 00:02:31.159
really work with Claude

00:02:31.159 --> 00:02:33.320
to become the technician

00:02:33.320 --> 00:02:34.719
that we leave behind.

00:02:36.559 --> 00:02:38.400
We see it like a garden

00:02:38.400 --> 00:02:39.320
and you're not really

00:02:39.320 --> 00:02:40.239
aware of the gardener

00:02:40.239 --> 00:02:42.079
that's silently keeping this

00:02:42.079 --> 00:02:44.199
whole harmony working.

00:02:46.960 --> 00:02:48.320
When you start talking to Claude,

00:02:48.320 --> 00:02:49.440
you see the world

00:02:49.440 --> 00:02:50.559
in a completely different way.

00:02:51.280 --> 00:02:54.079
Claude's read every science paper

00:02:54.079 --> 00:02:55.599
that is about bubbles,

00:02:55.599 --> 00:02:56.639
or it seems that way,

00:02:56.880 --> 00:02:59.239
and so we can talk to Claude about

00:02:59.239 --> 00:03:00.000
why are the bubbles

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:00.840
bouncing on water,

00:03:00.840 --> 00:03:01.559
why aren't they just

00:03:01.559 --> 00:03:02.079
joining the water?

00:03:02.360 --> 00:03:04.360
And once we understand

00:03:04.599 --> 00:03:05.559
the physics

00:03:05.559 --> 00:03:06.639
and the chemistry behind that,

00:03:06.880 --> 00:03:09.679
we're able to go much further

00:03:09.679 --> 00:03:10.599
with the work

00:03:10.599 --> 00:03:11.800
and much deeper,

00:03:11.800 --> 00:03:13.000
because it's like having

00:03:13.000 --> 00:03:14.320
an expert

00:03:14.320 --> 00:03:16.320
there on hand in the studio.

00:03:16.320 --> 00:03:17.760
So it very much feels

00:03:17.760 --> 00:03:19.000
like a team member

00:03:19.000 --> 00:03:20.039
in that sense.

00:03:27.719 --> 00:03:28.840
In the end,

00:03:28.840 --> 00:03:29.840
The Moon Underwater

00:03:29.840 --> 00:03:31.239
is about impermanence,

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:32.880
a reminder

00:03:32.880 --> 00:03:34.320
that nothing lasts forever.

00:03:37.119 --> 00:03:38.440
This is technology

00:03:38.440 --> 00:03:39.960
returning to the realm of nature.

00:03:40.639 --> 00:03:42.639
Alive, fleeting,

00:03:42.639 --> 00:03:44.000
and full of mystery.

00:03:44.639 --> 00:03:46.199
An art of disappearing

00:03:46.199 --> 00:03:48.079
that makes us feel more present

00:03:48.079 --> 00:03:49.840
while it lasts.

